==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spiralozooid
<hw>Spi*ra`lo*zo"oid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spiral</ets> + <ets>zooid</ets>. So called because they often
have a spiral form when contracted.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of the special defensive zooids of certain hydroids. They have the form
of long, slender tentacles, and bear lasso cells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spirant</ent>⟦br⟧
